Key Match Events: Jose Altuve and Jeremy Peña homered
Houston increased its lead in the AL West to 5 1/2 games over Seattle
Kevin Newman homered off Kikuchi in the fourth to put Arizona up 3-1
Houston rallied for four runs against Eduardo Rodriguez in the bottom half
Chas McCormick tied the game with a two-run single
Yordan Alvarez’s two-out RBI single put the Astros on top
After an error, Alex Bregman capped the flurry with a bases-loaded walk
Eugenio Suárez hit his 25th homer in the sixth to bring Arizona within a run
The Astros broke open the game with the help of Peña’s three-run drive into the Houston bullpen in right-center field
Miscellaneous Highlights: Arizona, which has dropped three straight and seven of 10, holds a half-game edge over the New York Mets for the second National League wild card
Others: Yusei Kikuchi (8-9) allowed four runs and seven hits over six innings. He struck out six, giving him a career-high 183 strikeouts this season
Kikuchi has a 3.07 ERA since joining the Astros in a trade from the Toronto Blue Jays on July 29, with a 32.1% strikeout rate
Eduardo Rodriguez (2-2) faced 10 batters and needed 47 pitches to get through the inning. Houston loaded the bases without a hit
Dylan Floro was charged with all five Houston runs in the sixth
